1050
01:50:53,881 --> 01:51:00,787
[SPEAKER_15]: But when you're seeing the mismanagement of funds to the levels that we're seeing, with the loss of revenue that we were

1051
01:51:01,140 --> 01:51:13,770
[SPEAKER_15]: we were getting from Armstrong Ambulance, for instance, the questions that we have with our contracted services, and how many contracts we're hearing that aren't in compliance today.

1052
01:51:15,731 --> 01:51:28,701
[SPEAKER_15]: When we see the monies that are leaving the city because of lawsuits and settlements, when you see us fighting 40B projects, which you can't beat, you can't win,

1053
01:51:29,925 --> 01:51:39,850
[SPEAKER_15]: 40B projects, 40Bs were created to support the mission, which is helping affordable housing.

1054
01:51:41,150 --> 01:51:48,673
[SPEAKER_15]: What we're seeing now is the mayor losing that and then filing appeals, knowing you're going to lose again.

1055
01:51:51,135 --> 01:51:58,358
[SPEAKER_15]: So it's going to be interesting to see where the funding is going and how much money this city has wasted.

1056
01:51:59,243 --> 01:52:01,924
[SPEAKER_15]: and fighting personal vendetta, as it seems.

1057
01:52:02,684 --> 01:52:06,165
[SPEAKER_15]: And again, Mr. President, I know it was KP law.

1058
01:52:07,485 --> 01:52:08,586
[SPEAKER_15]: We've had a city solicitor.

1059
01:52:08,626 --> 01:52:09,546
[SPEAKER_15]: Then it's KP law.

1060
01:52:10,066 --> 01:52:14,628
[SPEAKER_15]: And we has anybody seen an actual month to month recently?

1061
01:52:15,328 --> 01:52:15,788
[SPEAKER_15]: Has anyone?

1062
01:52:16,841 --> 01:52:21,423
[SPEAKER_15]: So that's when normal communities, councils, you get a budget.

1063
01:52:21,463 --> 01:52:26,406
[SPEAKER_15]: And every month, you get the breakdown of where we're spending money on a month-to-month basis.

1064
01:52:26,926 --> 01:52:28,326
[SPEAKER_15]: We used to get it once in a while.

1065
01:52:28,346 --> 01:52:33,429
[SPEAKER_15]: And they used to read through and used to go down the column on the right and say, KP law, KP law, KP law.

1066
01:52:33,509 --> 01:52:34,409
[SPEAKER_15]: And they used to highlight it.

1067
01:52:34,729 --> 01:52:38,371
[SPEAKER_15]: And it was great, because in the school department, they would have KP law.

1068
01:52:38,411 --> 01:52:40,552
[SPEAKER_15]: In the fire line, it would have KP law.

1069
01:52:40,832 --> 01:52:42,293
[SPEAKER_15]: In this department, you have KP law.

1070
01:52:42,773 --> 01:52:46,075
[SPEAKER_15]: But in the law line, it still fell into that budget line.

1071
01:52:46,963 --> 01:52:48,844
[SPEAKER_15]: So we were seeing where the money was going.

1072
01:52:50,826 --> 01:52:55,208
[SPEAKER_15]: So we know hundreds of thousands of millions of dollars have gone out the door to KP Law.

1073
01:52:56,029 --> 01:53:01,452
[SPEAKER_15]: But from what I gather now, we now have another law firm that the city is using.

1074
01:53:01,472 --> 01:53:14,321
[SPEAKER_15]: From what I gather from our workforce that is going to these legal hearings is that these law firms are coming in with teams of two, three, four attorneys.

1075
01:53:15,610 --> 01:53:19,516
[SPEAKER_15]: And I'm sure they're not saying, we're only gonna charge it for one attorney.

1076
01:53:21,799 --> 01:53:30,513
[SPEAKER_15]: So it's imperative that we get these numbers, because I will wait for the period, but then if we do not get these numbers, I will ask my colleagues.

1077
01:53:32,160 --> 01:53:56,547
[SPEAKER_15]: Again, to vote for an audit, an outside audit to come in, to look at situations exactly like this, look at situations exactly what's happening with the money we lost to Armstrong Ambulance, look at the funding with the trash contracts, look at these other contracts that are falling off and seeing where we've lost money and why we're in such dire straits other than the climate that we're in.

1078
01:53:57,287 --> 01:53:59,408
[SPEAKER_15]: Because there is something amiss here.

1079
01:54:00,450 --> 01:54:02,491
[SPEAKER_15]: And I've been saying this for years now.

1080
01:54:03,272 --> 01:54:06,934
[SPEAKER_15]: The mismanagement of this community's finances are frightening.

1081
01:54:07,955 --> 01:54:21,864
[SPEAKER_15]: And this information that was gathered, this information that was put down, and then was read by my council president, thankfully, it should speak volumes.

1082
01:54:22,425 --> 01:54:25,927
[SPEAKER_15]: I know a lot of people tune out in the first two minutes, but read it.

1083
01:54:27,989 --> 01:54:35,975
[SPEAKER_15]: Look at the numbers from when this mayor took office, and look at who she hurts, and look at who she attacks, and look how much money it's costing us.

1084
01:54:37,456 --> 01:54:43,001
[SPEAKER_15]: Because it's going to be important as we move forward, especially in this budget season.

1085
01:54:43,021 --> 01:54:50,827
[SPEAKER_15]: Because if I don't get these numbers, I will, for one, will not support any budget that this mayor creates to come to this podium and ask for my support.

1086
01:54:51,788 --> 01:54:52,328
[SPEAKER_15]: I can't do it.

1087
01:54:53,373 --> 01:54:54,553
[SPEAKER_15]: So thank you, Mr. President.

1088
01:54:54,813 --> 01:55:17,158
[SPEAKER_15]: So again, I would ask for those pieces also be added in, that we get the breakdown of the law firms and break their invoices down for any private investigators that are paid out through those law offices, and then

1089
01:55:18,668 --> 01:55:23,269
[SPEAKER_15]: Ask for an update on insurance premiums, where it was in 2019, where we are today.

1090
01:55:24,110 --> 01:55:34,573
[SPEAKER_15]: And then if I can make an amendment to while we're here, because I know that we've been asking the city solicitor's office, city solicitor office, well, we don't have a city solicitor again.

1091
01:55:35,113 --> 01:55:40,914
[SPEAKER_15]: So one, if we can get an update and where we are when it comes to the hiring of a city solicitor.

1092
01:55:41,715 --> 01:55:46,716
[SPEAKER_15]: And two, who is going to report to us

1093
01:55:48,101 --> 01:55:50,663
[SPEAKER_15]: in place of the city solicitor.

1094
01:55:51,144 --> 01:55:58,450
[SPEAKER_15]: I know that our friend that is running that office today, it would be just unfair for her to do that.

1095
01:55:58,530 --> 01:56:00,132
[SPEAKER_15]: So thank you, Mr. President.

1096
01:56:02,354 --> 01:56:03,295
[SPEAKER_25]: Thank you, Councilor Scarpelli.

1097
01:56:03,315 --> 01:56:09,160
[SPEAKER_25]: And Councilor Hangiff, if I may, just before you go, you know, we're a long way from 2024 here, and I think

1098
01:56:12,223 --> 01:56:20,530
[SPEAKER_25]: Something that got lost in those debates in 2024 was that two things can be true at the same time.

1099
01:56:23,193 --> 01:56:29,859
[SPEAKER_25]: And we spent a lot of time, Councilor Schiappale and I, and many of us going back and forth and saying,

1100
01:56:33,220 --> 01:56:42,064
[SPEAKER_25]: we were making an argument around the structural deficit and the structural issues that cities and towns across the commonwealth are facing when it comes to our finances.

1101
01:56:43,245 --> 01:56:58,732
[SPEAKER_25]: And instead of having the conversation about is the city's litigation approach the right approach, what's the fiscal impact of management decisions like that, instead it was if you're saying that, that means that you don't believe in the structural deficit.

1102
01:56:59,072 --> 01:57:01,173
[SPEAKER_25]: And I don't think that that was ever true.

1103
01:57:02,168 --> 01:57:27,913
[SPEAKER_25]: And I think we, for years now, have been put in this situation where we felt, I'll speak for myself, I felt the need to defend decisions made by the administration to avoid the appearance that, basically to justify that the larger structural question of

1104
01:57:29,363 --> 01:57:31,885
[SPEAKER_25]: being an underfunded city is true.

1105
01:57:32,486 --> 01:57:38,051
[SPEAKER_25]: And I think it's actually true that you can be an underfunded city and bad decisions can be happening, right?

1106
01:57:39,012 --> 01:57:41,755
[SPEAKER_25]: And that's where we're coming to here.

1107
01:57:42,630 --> 01:58:01,824
[SPEAKER_25]: You know, as Councilor Scarpelli noted, right, you look at the top lines of the budget and it seems like the law department is under budget, but then there's other places where legal expenses are happening or settlements are being paid out through insurance and that's going to affect us in the future or more claims are being filed, that kind of thing.

1108
01:58:03,445 --> 01:58:06,508
[SPEAKER_25]: But I think the larger point here is

1109
01:58:08,323 --> 01:58:17,868
[SPEAKER_25]: Even if none of these lawsuits ever happened and nothing was going on, the city wouldn't have saved enough money to address the fact that we're facing 30 or 40 years of underfunding.

1110
01:58:18,588 --> 01:58:36,678
[SPEAKER_25]: But when we talk about excellence and accountability and making sure that people believe in government, it's a lot harder to make the case about underfunding and structural deficits when there's other stuff that's happening that makes people think, well, what are they doing with that money anyway?

1111
01:58:37,510 --> 01:58:42,136
[SPEAKER_25]: Right and that's that's the issue here you know.

1112
01:58:44,682 --> 01:58:49,784
[SPEAKER_25]: Two years ago, I looked at the numbers and I said, well, they make sense, right?

1113
01:58:50,344 --> 01:58:55,126
[SPEAKER_25]: And I trusted in the information that was being presented to us and that is being presented to the community.

1114
01:58:56,026 --> 01:59:06,110
[SPEAKER_25]: And in 2025, we hired a city solicitor and it wasn't the most, I didn't agree with him on everything, but we had someone in that office and we were building a working relationship.

1115
01:59:06,590 --> 01:59:11,132
[SPEAKER_25]: And then right as his probationary period is coming up, he's gone.

1116
01:59:12,270 --> 01:59:17,913
[SPEAKER_25]: And now we're back to this situation that we were in for years, where there's no city solicitor who's representing the city.

1117
01:59:17,973 --> 01:59:35,682
[SPEAKER_25]: We're back to outside legal counsel, racking up outside legal fees, like we have to go to them every time for one-on-one things, and communications get missed, and there's more lawsuits, and there's more issues, and there's more claims.

1118
01:59:36,023 --> 01:59:39,244
[SPEAKER_25]: And I don't feel the same way that I felt two years ago,

1119
01:59:41,970 --> 01:59:48,276
[SPEAKER_25]: that I have the trust and faith that the right decisions are being made when it comes to litigation.

1120
01:59:48,696 --> 01:59:55,562
[SPEAKER_25]: You know, Councilor Scarpella uses the word audit, I would use a different word, independent review, bring in an expert, look at what's going on.

1121
01:59:55,762 --> 01:59:58,364
[SPEAKER_25]: Is this happening in any other city in Massachusetts?

1122
01:59:58,384 --> 02:00:01,887
[SPEAKER_25]: Is this the way that any other city in Massachusetts is approaching

1123
02:00:02,708 --> 02:00:04,249
[SPEAKER_25]: legal expenses and litigation.

1124
02:00:04,909 --> 02:00:08,872
[SPEAKER_25]: Is this what labor relations looks like in any other city in Massachusetts, right?

1125
02:00:10,593 --> 02:00:13,575
[SPEAKER_25]: And I don't think that means we didn't need an override.

1126
02:00:14,255 --> 02:00:17,337
[SPEAKER_25]: And I don't think that means we don't have a structural deficit and we don't have underfunding.

1127
02:00:18,458 --> 02:00:30,605
[SPEAKER_25]: But it's a lot harder to make the case on the facts around the budget and structural deficits and really funding our city, supporting our workers, doing the things we need to do as a city, when

1128
02:00:32,483 --> 02:00:38,169
[SPEAKER_25]: other decisions and other operations and litigation is happening that undermines trust and faith that people have in their government.

1129
02:00:39,450 --> 02:00:42,473
[SPEAKER_25]: And we have big decisions coming up, right?

1130
02:00:43,134 --> 02:00:49,020
[SPEAKER_25]: There was a faith issue and a trust issue, and that's why we don't have a new fire station under construction right now.

1131
02:00:50,041 --> 02:00:55,226
[SPEAKER_25]: And we're going through an MSBA project that's going to be the biggest thing we've done in 50 years, and we need a new high school.

1132
02:00:56,307 --> 02:00:58,289
[SPEAKER_25]: And we can't have trust and faith issues.

1133
02:00:58,329 --> 02:01:05,256
[SPEAKER_25]: We need people to understand that that process is going well, that yes, it's a major investment, but that we need to do it.

1134
02:01:06,497 --> 02:01:18,569
[SPEAKER_25]: And if there's other things going on around litigation and questions being raised about our expenses and another year without a city solicitor, it's going to be harder to convince some people to do big things.

1135
02:01:20,201 --> 02:01:23,863
[SPEAKER_25]: And so, I appreciate being able to work together.

1136
02:01:23,963 --> 02:01:29,387
[SPEAKER_25]: I think that these questions that are being asked here, the data that we're seeing demand that we ask these questions.

1137
02:01:30,227 --> 02:01:32,989
[SPEAKER_25]: And I want to see the answers.

1138
02:01:33,989 --> 02:01:35,791
[SPEAKER_25]: I want to understand what the impact is.

1139
02:01:36,711 --> 02:01:42,875
[SPEAKER_25]: And, you know, maybe when you lay all the facts out, it doesn't look great, but at least the facts are out there.

1140
02:01:43,777 --> 02:01:51,040
[SPEAKER_25]: And I don't feel like I have to go digging into line items to try to justify and defend practices that I never even had a role in, right?

1141
02:01:51,900 --> 02:02:02,885
[SPEAKER_25]: That's another thing that this council has been put in a really bad position, is defending decisions that we didn't have any voice in because we're trying to keep faith.

1142
02:02:03,325 --> 02:02:07,047
[SPEAKER_25]: We're trying to maintain trust, we're trying to make sure that people believe that government

1143
02:02:08,597 --> 02:02:13,362
[SPEAKER_25]: And city government is doing its best and trying to solve big problems.

1144
02:02:13,862 --> 02:02:16,245
[SPEAKER_25]: So I hope that we can get answers that show what's happened.

1145
02:02:16,265 --> 02:02:20,609
[SPEAKER_25]: I hope we can get an independent review that shows how we should be acting differently.

1146
02:02:21,069 --> 02:02:26,335
[SPEAKER_25]: And I appreciate that we're working together across that issue because, again, two things can be true at once.

1147
02:02:27,436 --> 02:02:28,637
[SPEAKER_25]: The city needs more funding.

1148
02:02:28,677 --> 02:02:30,078
[SPEAKER_25]: Our departments need more staff.

1149
02:02:30,138 --> 02:02:31,460
[SPEAKER_25]: We have structural deficits.

1150
02:02:32,555 --> 02:02:47,921
[SPEAKER_25]: And from all the evidence in front of me, this city's approach to litigation and labor relations is not one that brings trust and that is the most fiscally responsible, and not one that I'm seeing modeled in any other city here in Massachusetts.

1151
02:02:48,021 --> 02:02:51,462
[SPEAKER_25]: So I want these answers, and I'm glad that we're working together to find them.

1152
02:02:53,063 --> 02:02:53,663
[SPEAKER_25]: Councilor Tseng.

1153
02:02:55,064 --> 02:02:55,444
[SPEAKER_23]: Thank you.

1154
02:02:56,064 --> 02:03:00,546
[SPEAKER_23]: I wanted to thank you two for your words and for

1155
02:03:01,888 --> 02:03:12,535
[SPEAKER_23]: putting together this, you know, very resourced resolution and, you know, having me, inviting me to look at it and co-sponsor.

1156
02:03:13,816 --> 02:03:17,759
[SPEAKER_23]: There are a lot of words in this resolution.

1157
02:03:18,859 --> 02:03:23,442
[SPEAKER_23]: There are a lot of words that have been said and I think are on the dot.

1158
02:03:25,384 --> 02:03:29,767
[SPEAKER_23]: But I think underneath all of what we're saying is we need more oversight.

1159
02:03:31,182 --> 02:03:34,863
[SPEAKER_23]: Residents trust us with their tax dollars, their schools, their streets.

1160
02:03:35,603 --> 02:03:41,004
[SPEAKER_23]: And with that trust comes a responsibility to understand the full financial picture of our city.

1161
02:03:42,284 --> 02:03:49,426
[SPEAKER_23]: And over the last few years, as this resolution shows, the volume of litigation facing Medford has increased.

1162
02:03:50,026 --> 02:03:53,807
[SPEAKER_23]: We see lawsuits, labor filings, administrative matters.

1163
02:03:53,907 --> 02:03:57,527
[SPEAKER_23]: And these are a part of governing as a complex and growing city.

1164
02:03:58,108 --> 02:04:00,088
[SPEAKER_23]: It's not unusual for disagreements to happen.

1165
02:04:00,768 --> 02:04:09,373
[SPEAKER_23]: But what does matter and what is unusual in the volume is how we manage the situation.

1166
02:04:10,133 --> 02:04:23,220
[SPEAKER_23]: Right now, our council doesn't receive regular comprehensive reporting on the total scope of our litigation exposure, what we're spending, what's pending, how it affects long-term planning.

1167
02:04:24,193 --> 02:04:31,867
[SPEAKER_23]: We know lawyers are expensive, but what we can't do is stand by instead of finding ways to reduce costs for our city.

1168
02:04:33,065 --> 02:04:41,833
[SPEAKER_23]: And this idea has real implications, like Councilor Scarpelli and like President Bears was just saying, we need to build trust.

1169
02:04:42,634 --> 02:04:55,045
[SPEAKER_23]: Every dollar we spend on prolonged legal conflicts is a dollar that we can't spend fixing our structural deficit, investing somewhere else in classrooms and road repairs and safer streets and services our residents rely on.

1170
02:04:55,805 --> 02:05:04,989
[SPEAKER_23]: And in some cases, we're worried that the city's position in the lawsuits are positions that are, that have inhibited revenue growth in the city.

1171
02:05:06,389 --> 02:05:10,951
[SPEAKER_23]: We've worked hard to make meaningful investments in this community over the last few years.

1172
02:05:11,611 --> 02:05:23,516
[SPEAKER_23]: And protecting that progress and building the trust that we need in our community to tackle systemic underfunding and to take on big projects like a new high school requires clarity and it requires discipline.

1173
02:05:25,183 --> 02:05:27,766
[SPEAKER_23]: Strong cities are built on strong working relationships.

1174
02:05:28,107 --> 02:05:33,894
[SPEAKER_23]: When disputes escalate and linger, they also consume time and resources and energy.

1175
02:05:34,314 --> 02:05:38,119
[SPEAKER_23]: They create uncertainty for the families of those who work in the city.

1176
02:05:38,519 --> 02:05:42,203
[SPEAKER_23]: They strain the very systems we depend on to deliver services.

1177
02:05:43,305 --> 02:05:45,027
[SPEAKER_23]: And like Councilor Scarpelli said,

1178
02:05:45,660 --> 02:05:51,044
[SPEAKER_23]: Morale is low, and too many workers have told us that they don't feel heard or appreciated.

1179
02:05:52,025 --> 02:06:06,355
[SPEAKER_23]: If better reporting helps us identify patterns, strengthen internal processes, and resolve issues earlier and more constructively, that benefits the entire city, from the people doing the work every day to the residents they serve.

1180
02:06:07,864 --> 02:06:17,026
[SPEAKER_23]: Something that has been said in the city council, and it's not original, but it's been said recently a lot, is that sunlight is the best disinfectant.

1181
02:06:19,286 --> 02:06:20,567
[SPEAKER_23]: Transparency builds trust.

1182
02:06:21,527 --> 02:06:26,908
[SPEAKER_23]: If our practices are prudent and necessary, regular reporting will show that.

1183
02:06:27,888 --> 02:06:36,270
[SPEAKER_23]: If there are opportunities to improve coordination or risk management, this gives us the information to do that thoughtfully and responsibly.

1184
02:06:38,090 --> 02:06:40,271
[SPEAKER_23]: I actually find this resolution pretty measured.

1185
02:06:40,891 --> 02:06:42,572
[SPEAKER_23]: It protects attorney-client privilege.

1186
02:06:42,652 --> 02:06:49,294
[SPEAKER_23]: It asks for a comprehensive report, quarterly updates, and an independent review of litigation costs and practices.

1187
02:06:49,994 --> 02:06:55,696
[SPEAKER_23]: These are tools that support stability and accountability in any well-run organization.

1188
02:06:57,216 --> 02:07:01,918
[SPEAKER_23]: Oversight and good management go hand in hand, and trust comes with verification.

1189
02:07:03,102 --> 02:07:18,048
[SPEAKER_23]: I believe that our shared goal on the city council and in the city writ large is a financially stable city, a strong and respectful working relationships, and a government that residents can feel confident in.

1190
02:07:18,068 --> 02:07:20,969
[SPEAKER_23]: I think this resolution is a step towards that.

1191
02:07:25,751 --> 02:07:26,651
[SPEAKER_25]: Thank you, Councilor Tseng.

1192
02:07:27,171 --> 02:07:28,552
[SPEAKER_25]: Councilor Molina, I saw you earlier.

1193
02:07:28,572 --> 02:07:29,252
[SPEAKER_25]: Do you still want to go?

1194
02:07:31,931 --> 02:07:58,088
[SPEAKER_20]: What I wanted to kind of follow up is, A, to thank you for putting this all together as someone who's kind of obviously new to the council, but seeing some of these things ad hoc, some of these different lawsuits, actually seeing it laid out in this manner of the increase of what's happened since 2019, the different areas in which you've been impacted with it, it was really eye-opening to see it all put together in this way, so I appreciate that it's highlighted in that way.

1195
02:07:58,581 --> 02:08:07,025
[SPEAKER_20]: But I also definitely agree about trying to have that budget line put together so that we can actually see what that overarching impact is.

1196
02:08:07,045 --> 02:08:13,127
[SPEAKER_20]: And I had originally put it on to Councilor Scarpelli when you said the insurance premiums.

1197
02:08:13,167 --> 02:08:14,828
[SPEAKER_20]: That was something that pops in my head and also.

1198
02:08:15,405 --> 02:08:20,932
[SPEAKER_20]: You know, what are we going to do without a city solicitor and having someone come up and be able to present this information as well.

1199
02:08:21,713 --> 02:08:32,147
[SPEAKER_20]: I think being able to get a better sense of when we're going to see or know or hear anything about a new city solicitor which seems to be obviously as this has been outlined.

1200
02:08:32,981 --> 02:08:36,863
[SPEAKER_20]: pretty impactful position for all of us, I think is also really important.

1201
02:08:36,963 --> 02:08:55,110
[SPEAKER_20]: So I just appreciate all three of you putting this together, the depth of which it took of putting this information all in one place, because I think it's important not only for us, but certainly for the residents to see exactly where some of this money is going towards, and we need to figure out

1202
02:08:55,605 --> 02:09:03,654
[SPEAKER_20]: how we can really address this moving forward and have a better sense of what is actually happening with a lot of these different litigations.

1203
02:09:03,714 --> 02:09:05,095
[SPEAKER_20]: So, thank you.

1204
02:09:07,158 --> 02:09:07,978
[SPEAKER_25]: Thank you, Councilor Malauulu.

1205
02:09:09,140 --> 02:09:11,843
[SPEAKER_25]: Any further comments or questions by members of the Council on this paper?

1206
02:09:13,296 --> 02:09:14,817
[SPEAKER_25]: Seeing none, we'll go to public participation.

1207
02:09:14,857 --> 02:09:16,277
[SPEAKER_25]: We have two hands on Zoom.

