1567
02:41:21,749 --> 02:41:29,834
[SPEAKER_25]: Whereas City of Medford is currently experiencing or scheduled to experience significant utility work on multiple roadways, including High Street, Boston Ave, Main Street, Riverside Ave, and Willis Ave.

1568
02:41:30,454 --> 02:41:35,357
[SPEAKER_25]: These projects are being undertaken by various entities, including MWRA, National Grid, other utilities.

1569
02:41:36,295 --> 02:41:42,361
[SPEAKER_25]: Whereas these infrastructure projects have significant impacts on traffic, parking, businesses, and daily lives of residents in affected neighborhoods.

1570
02:41:43,141 --> 02:41:48,887
[SPEAKER_25]: And whereas the council and residents would benefit from a comprehensive understanding of scope, timeline, phasing, and impacts of each project.

1571
02:41:49,427 --> 02:41:55,993
[SPEAKER_25]: And whereas the city currently posts some project information on the city website, and there is an opportunity to review and enhance how this information is shared with the public.

1572
02:41:56,513 --> 02:42:14,446
[SPEAKER_25]: be resolved by the Medford City Council that we respect the request that the Department of Public Works, in coordination with MWRA, National Grid, and other utilities, conducting or planning major infrastructure work, provide a briefing to the Council on current and upcoming major projects, including project scope, timelines, street-by-street phasing, and anticipated impact to residents.

1573
02:42:15,006 --> 02:42:27,069
[SPEAKER_25]: It further resolved that the council request a review of how and when project information is posted to the website and communicated with residents in affected areas with the goal of ensuring that neighbors receive timely, clear comprehensive notice well in advance of construction.

1574
02:42:27,129 --> 02:42:32,010
[SPEAKER_25]: And we had some good conversation about that earlier and I will recognize Councilor Scarpelli.

1575
02:42:32,390 --> 02:42:32,750
